com.cognos.CAM_AAA.authentication

Interface IRestorableVisa

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, IVisa, java.io.Serializable

    public interface IRestorableVisa
extends IVisa, java.io.Externalizable
    Defines the interface for a version of an IVisa that can be restored in a failover scenario so that the users session is maintained without having to login again

    • Method Detail

      • hasStateChanged

        boolean hasStateChanged()
        Is called to determine whether the visa has changed. If the state has changed, the server will update any cached versions for failover
        Returns:
        This method should return true after the object is created or if changes have been made to the state of the visa since the last time resetChangeIndicator() has been called.

      • resetChangeIndicator

        void resetChangeIndicator()
        Is called to reset the change indicator. A call to hasStateChanged() should return false when called immediately after calling resetChangeIndicator().
